      <section>
		 <br/>
                 <p><font size = 4><b>Welcome to the ADS-B Drone Collision Avoidance System Senior Project Page!!!</b></font></p>
                 <p>&mdash; <b> Edward, Andrew, Dat </b> &mdash;</p>
		 <p>
                 <br/>
		 Drones have increased in popularity and functionality over recent years, but they are still 
                 very  limited  in  the  commercial  domain  due  to  the  safety  implications  they  pose.  
                 <br/><br/>
                 Team  18  and  Nevada  Dynamics  
                 plan  to  use  ADS­-B readings and an algorithm using polar math, great circle calculations, 
                 and carefully designed thresholds  to  detect  and  avoid  collisions  with  fast­-moving  
                 aircraft  by  adjusting  a  drone’s  path or simply stopping the drone before any overlap in 
                 airspace occurs.
		 </p>
		 <br/>
         
		 <br/>
		 
